Package: UFSD
Version: 1.0.0
Maintainer: mgrossmann
Depends: MINIZIP NJE38
Homepage: https://github.com/mvslovers/ufsd
Description: MVS 3.8J Virtual Filesystem Daemon

This is mvslovers/ufsd: a cross-address-space filesystem server (STC/
subsystem) for MVS 3.8j. UFSD owns all BDAM disk I/O for UFS370
(Unix V7-style) filesystems and serves clients -- HTTPD, FTPD, batch,
TSO -- through the MVS subsystem interface (IEFSSREQ), presenting the
mounted disks as one unified directory tree.

This package installs in two jobs. #001JCL puts the UFSD, UFSDSSIR and
UFSDCLNP load modules into MVSLOVER.LOAD (the shared mvslovers load
library, created on first install; the STC procs use it as STEPLIB --
nothing is added to SYS2.LINKLIB), the STC procedures into
SYS2.PROCLIB(UFSD) and SYS2.PROCLIB(UFSDCLNP), and the default
configuration into SYS2.PARMLIB(UFSDPRM0). #002JCL uses NJE38's TSO
RECEIVE command (batch IKJEFT01) to restore six freshly-formatted,
empty UFS370 disk datasets (RECFM=U, 4096-byte blocks) referenced by
that configuration:

  UFSD.ROOT        1M  /           root filesystem
  HTTPD.WEBROOT    4M  /www        read-only web content
  IBMUSER.UFSHOME  2M  /u/ibmuser  home, writable by IBMUSER
  MVSCE01.UFSHOME  2M  /u/mvsce01  home, writable by MVSCE01
  MVSCE02.UFSHOME  2M  /u/mvsce02  home, writable by MVSCE02
  UFSD.SCRATCH     2M  /tmp        shared scratch, any user

A UFS370 filesystem's capacity is fixed at format time. For a bigger
disk, build an image on the host with ufsd-utils (github.com/
mvslovers/ufsd-utils), upload it, and add it to UFSDPRM0.

The disk datasets are allocated DISP=(NEW,CATLG): if one already
exists, that step fails with a JCL error rather than overwriting your
data. To reinstall an image, delete the dataset first and rerun.

To start the server run '/S UFSD' on the Hercules console; stop with
'/P UFSD'. Console commands: '/F UFSD,STATS|MOUNT LIST|HELP|SHUTDOWN'.
Mounts are configured in SYS2.PARMLIB(UFSDPRM0). If UFSD abends and
will not restart, run '/S UFSDCLNP' to clean up the SSCT and CSA, then
start UFSD again.
